      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom of the stems are turning this sickly yellow color but the top ones look okay. what's probably going on and how do i fix the soil?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The bottom leaves turning yellow could be a sign of poor drainage, a possible fungal infection, or nutrient deficiencies. First, check the soil moisture, as overwatering or underwatering can cause yellowing. If it's too wet, try to improve drainage and consider repotting with fresh, well-draining soil. If it's too dry, water your plants more consistently. If the problem persists, you might need to use a fungicide or consult with a local nursery for further advice. Remember, it's always better to err on the side of caution when dealing with plant health.",
